&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We seek to move the world forward through innovative thinking.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woolpert is an award-winning, global leader in architecture, engineering, and geospatial services. We blend design excellence with cutting-edge technology to deliver exceptional client value. Our team is passionate about their work and committed to building the next generation of industry leaders, and as a certified Great Place to Work&lt;a href=&quot;https://woolpert.com/about-us/culture/&quot;&gt;®&lt;/a&gt;, Woolpert embraces progress and innovation to create limitless opportunities for career growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woolpert is hiring an&lt;strong&gt; Accounts Payable &amp;amp; Expense Reviewer&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join our dynamic Finance Operations team. This is a &lt;strong&gt;remote position based in South Africa&lt;/strong&gt;, reporting to the Finance Operations Manager. The role is responsible for reviewing, validating, and processing employee expense reports in line with company travel and expense policies. Qualified candidates will be detail‑oriented, analytical, and have experience working with expense management or ERP systems. This role requires working US business hours, from 2:00 PM to 11:00 PM (SAST).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review employee expense reports submitted through the ERP or expense management system to ensure accuracy and completeness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify that all expenses comply with company travel, entertainment, and expense reimbursement policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure required supporting documentation (receipts, invoices, and approvals) is attached and meets policy requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate expense coding to the correct cost centers, departments, projects, and spend categories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor approval workflows to ensure expense reports are reviewed and approved within established timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, flag, and escalate non‑compliant, duplicate, or questionable expenses as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with employees and internal stakeholders to resolve discrepancies, missing documentation, or policy‑related questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate documentation and audit trails for all reviewed expense transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support month‑end and quarter‑end close activities related to expense reporting, as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to internal controls, compliance standards, and confidentiality requirements at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in expense processing, accounts payable, or financial operations (preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with expense management or ERP systems such as Concur, Coupa, Microsoft Dynamics 365, SAP, Oracle, Workday, or similar platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, or a related field preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant certifications in bookkeeping, accounts payable, or financial systems will be advantageous.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of expense reimbursement and travel &amp;amp; entertainment (T&amp;amp;E) policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High attention to detail with strong organizational and time‑management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to follow established procedures and apply policies consistently and fairly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good written and verbal communication skills in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple tasks and meet processing deadlines in a fast‑paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic proficiency in Microsoft Excel and other office productivity tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;st

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We seek to move the world forward through innovative thinking.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woolpert is an award-winning, global leader in architecture, engineering, and geospatial services. We blend design excellence with cutting-edge technology to deliver exceptional client value. Our team is passionate about their work and committed to building the next generation of industry leaders, and as a certified Great Place to Work&lt;a href=&quot;https://woolpert.com/about-us/culture/&quot;&gt;®&lt;/a&gt;, Woolpert embraces progress and innovation to create limitless opportunities for career growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Woolpert is hiring an Aerial Sensor Operator to join our dynamic Aerial Acquisitions team based out of our Dayton office. This position reports to the Geospatial Team Leader and is responsible for sensor operation and reporting for airborne mapping missions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MUST be willing to travel on a rotating travel schedule of 21 days on and 14 days off with both domestic and international travel required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot; data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;We are unable to provide visa sponsorship for this position. &amp;nbsp;Applicants must already possess work authorization in the country the job is located.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Participate in ground and flight operations efforts as needed, including mission planning, execution, briefing, debriefing, communications, and safety. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Ensure proper collection of data for accuracy and quality. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Understand the collection of tactical and wide area mapping. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Comply with all governing regulations and work in accordance with established operating procedures and practices. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Download, edit, and troubleshoot collected sensor data while in the field. Set up and operate ground GPS base stations and flight planning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We seek to move the world forward through innovative thinking.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woolpert is an award-winning, global leader in architecture, engineering, and geospatial services. We blend design excellence with cutting-edge technology to deliver exceptional client value. Our team is passionate about their work and committed to building the next generation of industry leaders, and as a certified Great Place to Work&lt;a href=&quot;https://woolpert.com/about-us/culture/&quot;&gt;®&lt;/a&gt;, Woolpert embraces progress and innovation to create limitless opportunities for career growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Seeking a new career challenge? Woolpert Africa is looking for you! We are hiring&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Architects and Senior Technologists&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join&amp;nbsp;a&amp;nbsp;dynamic Buildings Team at our Johannesburg, South Africa office. This position reports&amp;nbsp;to Project Leads in the UK and US and supports the Regional Team Leader and is responsible for leading a team&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;the development and delivery of all project deliverables.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As an Architect at Woolpert, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop&amp;nbsp;project deliverables, from concept through completion, and&amp;nbsp;see the project through construction and close out.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in tandem with&amp;nbsp;global staff&amp;nbsp;and Project Leads,&amp;nbsp;as well as an interdisciplinary team of partners to deliver high performing, complex, and challenging projects for some of the world’s largest technology clients. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s degree in Architecture or Bachelor’s degree in Architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Between 4 - 6 years of architectural experience across stages of design and construction.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on&amp;nbsp;medium&amp;nbsp;to large-sized projects such as retail, multi-family residential, or commercial developments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess strong design,&amp;nbsp;coordination,&amp;nbsp;and problem-solving skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to&amp;nbsp;staying&amp;nbsp;informed on the latest architectural technologies, materials, and sustainability practices.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency&amp;nbsp;in the use of Autodesk Revit for project development; we are a&amp;nbsp;Revit office and use this software to its full capabilities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, Teams, etc.) and Bluebeam.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-developed organizational skills, and the&amp;nbsp;ability&amp;nbsp;and experience&amp;nbsp;to prioritize&amp;nbsp;tasks&amp;nbsp;and act independently.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal, written, and graphic communication skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to work and collaborate with global teams.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills and Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate should be registered with SACAP.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unique Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Certified as a Great Place to Work®, Woolpert is one of the fastest growing architecture, engineering, and geospatial (AEG) companies in the world. With over 60 offices and countless projects around the globe, Woolpert makes a real difference at home and abroad. In addition to offering competitive pay, we provide employees with a robust set of unique benefits, including:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diverse experiences: Work on meaningful projects that improve quality of life around the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Freedom to work program:&amp;nbsp;Work

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We seek to move the world forward through innovative thinking.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woolpert is an award-winning, global leader in architecture, engineering, and geospatial services. We blend design excellence with cutting-edge technology to deliver exceptional client value. Our team is passionate about their work and committed to building the next generation of industry leaders, and as a certified Great Place to Work&lt;a href=&quot;https://woolpert.com/about-us/culture/&quot;&gt;®&lt;/a&gt;, Woolpert embraces progress and innovation to create limitless opportunities for career growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Woolpert Inc. in Coral Gables, Florida is seeking multiple Architect/Designers to prepare graphics, presentations, contract drawings and/or regulatory submissions; organize and maintain project record information and drawings; participate in design team meetings and client presentations; coordinate technical services with clients, project consultants and engineers; and create promotional materials and respond to Requests for Proposals as required. Telecommuting permitted two days a week. At a minimum, the position requires a Master’s Degree in Architecture or foreign equivalent. Through Master’s level education, employee must possess expertise with architectural software (such as Revit or Autocad). Resumes to &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:askHR@woolpert.com&quot;&gt;askHR@woolpert.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(236, 240, 241);&quot;&gt;#LI-DNI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Find out more about what Woolpert has to offer here:&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;http://woolpert.com/about-us/&quot;&gt;http://woolpert.com/about-us/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Woolpert is an equal-opportunity employer.&lt;/strong&gt; Woolpert is committed to the full inclusion of all individuals. We recruit, train, compensate, and promote regardless of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, disability, age, veteran status, and other protected status as required by applicable law.&amp;nbsp; You may view more about EEO on our website: &lt;a href=&quot;https://woolpert.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Equal-Employment-Opportunity-The-Law.pdf&quot;&gt;Equal-Employment-Opportunity-The-Law.pdf&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://woolpert.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/EEO-is-the-Law-Supplement.pdf&quot;&gt;EEO is the Law Poster Supplement&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who require an accommodation throughout the application and interview process should request this in advance by contacting &lt;u&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:askhr@woolpert.com&quot;&gt;askhr@woolpert.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you need to reschedule or cancel your interview, please reach out to your recruiter by contacting &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:recruiting@woolpert.com&quot;&gt;recruiting@woolpert.com&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;To all agencies:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please, no phone calls or emails to any employee of Woolpert or any of our subsidiaries about this requisition. All resumes submitted by search firms/employment agencies to any employee at Woolpert via email, the internet, or in any form and/or method will be deemed the sole property of Woolpert, unless such search firms/employment agencies were engaged by Woolpert&#39;s Talent Acquisition Team for this requisition and a valid agreement is in place. In the event a candidate who was submitted outside of Woolpert&#39;s applicant process is hired, no fee or payment of any kind will be paid.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We seek to move the world forward through innovative thinking.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woolpert is an award-winning, global leader in architecture, engineering, and geospatial services. We blend design excellence with cutting-edge technology to deliver exceptional client value. Our team is passionate about their work and committed to building the next generation of industry leaders, and as a certified Great Place to Work&lt;a href=&quot;https://woolpert.com/about-us/culture/&quot;&gt;®&lt;/a&gt;, Woolpert embraces progress and innovation to create limitless opportunities for career growth.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2009, Greenbox Architecture is a leading Australian design practice specialising in mission-critical architecture across data centres, health, and life sciences, alongside commercial and workplace interiors. Now part of Woolpert, a global leader in Architecture, Engineering, and Geospatial (AEG), the team combines local design expertise with global capability. Woolpert has a strong and growing presence across Australia, building on its heritage as AAM, and delivers leading-edge solutions across infrastructure, environmental, and digital projects throughout Asia-Pacific.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ’Woolpack’ fosters a culture of innovation, inclusion, and ownership—exemplified by our celebrated Principal Program, which offers all employees, the opportunity to become company owners and share in the company’s growing success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Great Place to Work®!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re proud to be certified as a Great Place to Work® for the 9th time! We invest in advanced tools and professional development to empower our teams. Built on trust, respect, and shared success, our culture makes Woolpert more than a workplace it’s a community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The opportunity with us as an Architect/Designer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Architect/Designer to join our growing Sydney team. Reporting to one of our highly skilled Associates, you will be part of a collaborative team delivering complex, large-scale, mission-critical architectural projects, including data centres and specialised infrastructure. Our current portfolio includes projects ranging from $400k to over $3billion serving a variety of clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working on complex, multi-phase projects with a focus on achieving high-quality outcomes and compliance with regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involved in project delivery across detail design, documentation, coordination, and construction support, ensuring projects are delivered in line with design intent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with internal teams and external consultants to ensure alignment across all project stages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing and reviewing detailed drawings and models to support accurate project documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting project timelines, deliverables, and quality outcomes across multiple project phases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re looking for someone who has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years’ relevant architectural experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of Australian building codes.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong level of technical/construction knowledge is highly regarded.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of design and construction documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Revit proficiency is essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rendering (Enscape, Lumion) and Photoshop skills will also be highly regarded.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in complex commercial or large scale multi-residential projects is highly regarded.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
